<img class="wp-image-1140130 aligncenter" src="https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Cultism-e1549219620311-300x211.jpg?resize=640%2C450&#038;ssl=1" alt="Cultism" width="640" height="450" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Cultism-e1549219620311.jpg?resize=300%2C211&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Cultism-e1549219620311.jpg?resize=58%2C41&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Cultism-e1549219620311.jpg?resize=260%2C183&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Cultism-e1549219620311.jpg?resize=185%2C130&amp;ssl=1 185w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Cultism-e1549219620311.jpg?w=539&amp;ssl=1 539w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> Not less than six persons have been reportedly killed in some parts of Edo state by suspected armed herdsmen and cult related fight over supremacy. Two farmers in Odighi, Ovia North East local government area were allegedly killed by suspected herdsmen on their ways to their farms. An eyewitness, Hilary Omoregie, disclosed yesterday that “I am from Odigutue, a neighbouring community to Odighi and I was going to my village this when I saw people gathered around two dead bodies. It was gathered that the farmers were going to their farms when they were ambushed and shot by suspected herdsmen. The two bodies were later evacuated by police officials from Ekiadolor Police Division. Meanwhile, four persons have been killed since Easter Sunday as a result of continued clash between members of Eiye and Black Axe confraternities. A young man was Tuesday night reportedly shot dead at Ugbague lane by suspected rival cult members while another said to be a youth leader in Ward 12 Oredo local government area escaped being killed when his assailants also believed to be rival cult groups came for him. On Easter Sunday, a young man was reportedly trailed and shot while going to have his bath. When contacted on telephone over the cult killings, Edo state Police Commissioner, Lawal Jimeta, said he is yet to be briefed about the cult killings but that some persons have been arrested by the anti-cultism unit. On the killing of the farmers, the CP said they were hunters who went to the bush the previous night and their bodies were discovered yesterday morning adding that investigation has commenced on the incident. Vanguard News Nigeria. BENIN CITY - THERE is palpable tension in Odighi community, Ovia North-East Local Government Area of Edo State, after suspected herdsmen killed two persons including Pius Eromosele, a pastor attached to the Church of God Mission, in Benin City, the Edo State capital. April 8, 2018 In "News" UGHELLI - DESPITE claims by Delta State Commissioner of Police, CP, Hafiz Inuwa, that police were waiting autopsy report of exhumed corpses of the eight victims allegedly killed by herdsmen at Uwheru kingdom in Ughelli North Local Government Area, findings by Vanguard, yesterday, revealed that the investigation had been put… February 20, 2020 In "News" BENIN CITY—  No fewer than 10 persons were, yesterday, killed in Benin City, Edo State, as rival cult groups, Aye and Eiye confraternities, engaged in reprisal attacks. February 21, 2020 In "News"